Subject: Re: [VB] Emblem Clips?

I used "bonded washers" which are slightly concave metal washers with
a rubber washer glued to the "inside" of the concave part.  The ID
of the rubber washer is just a wee bit smaller than the metal one, so
they seal fairly well.

Everett Barnes wrote:
> I usually pick up some fiber buffers for over the shafts too - it protects
> the paint (or primer, haha).  One of my original emblems had the padded
> washers on there so I figure it's original?

